{
  "texts": [
    "We prepare the state on two physical qubits using a single entangling gate, together with single-qubit rotations, before measuring the state in varying single-qubit Pauli bases, P and Q, to conduct state tomography on the circuit output.",
    "Device overviewEncoded state data collection on ibm_peekskill v.2.4.0 spanned several days over a single region.",
    "During this time, monitoring experiments were interleaved with tomography data collection trials.",
    "Device coherence times for all qubits exceed about 100 μs and two-qubit errors per gate was found to range from 0.35% to 0.59%.",
    "Detailed monitoring of readout errors are provided in Extended Data Fig. 9f,g and time-averaged readout fidelities ranged from 98.1% to 99.6% for all qubits."
  ]
}